@page "/about"
@layout MarketingLayout

<PageTitle>About &mdash; NavTour</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="NavTour is an interactive demo platform built by Grupo Barrdega — a product-engineering team from Panama City with 30+ years across the Americas." />
</HeadContent>

<section class="nt-page-hero">
    <div class="nt-container">
        <span class="eyebrow">About NavTour</span>
        <h1>Built by a team that<br />knows enterprise sales <em>pain-first.</em></h1>
        <p class="lead">NavTour is a product of Grupo Barrdega — a product-engineering organization headquartered in Panama City, operating in 32 countries since 1990. We built NavTour because we needed it ourselves.</p>
        <div class="nt-hero-actions">
            <a href="/register" class="btn btn-orange btn-lg">Start building free &rarr;</a>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">Get in touch</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

@* ── MISSION ── *@
<section class="nt-section">
    <div class="nt-container" style="max-width:740px">
        <span class="eyebrow">Mission</span>
        <h2 style="margin-top:16px">Demos shouldn&rsquo;t be a dark art.</h2>
        <p style="margin-top:20px;font-size:1.08rem;line-height:1.75">
            Every revenue team we worked with had the same problem: great software, mediocre demos.
            Sales reps were building screen recordings by hand, sending decks that expired, and showing
            buyers a script instead of a product. NavTour replaces all of that with one system —
            capture, build, share, measure — that takes under two minutes to ship.
        </p>
        <p style="margin-top:16px;font-size:1.08rem;line-height:1.75">
            We&rsquo;re Americas-native, bilingual EN/ES by default, and built for the way enterprise
            deals actually work in Latin America — champions who forward links to five stakeholders,
            buying committees that can&rsquo;t get on a Zoom, and IT departments that require SOC&nbsp;2
            before they&rsquo;ll even look at a vendor demo.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

@* ── VALUES ── *@
<section class="nt-section" style="background:var(--nt-bg-alt)">
    <div class="nt-container">
        <span class="eyebrow">How we work</span>
        <div class="nt-card-grid" style="margin-top:32px">
            <div class="nt-card">
                <h3>Ship it live, not in staging</h3>
                <p>Every feature we show in NavTour exists in the deployed product. No mockups, no &ldquo;coming soon&rdquo; banners on live demo pages. We eat our own cooking.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-card">
                <h3>Americas-native, not Americas-adapted</h3>
                <p>Bilingual EN/ES is first-class, not an afterthought. Our support team speaks Spanish, our product defaults to the right timezone, and our compliance is SOC&nbsp;2 — not just &ldquo;GDPR-ish.&rdquo;</p>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-card">
                <h3>Revenue engineering, not just SaaS</h3>
                <p>We built NavTour while running our own pre-sales and customer success motions. Every feature exists because we needed it — not because a product manager estimated market size.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

@* ── STATS ── *@
<div class="nt-results">
    <div class="nt-container">
        <div class="nt-stats">
            <div class="nt-stat">
                <div class="lbl">Founded</div>
                <div class="n">1990</div>
                <p>Grupo Barrdega established in Panama City. Part of the P4 Software Cloud Suite.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-stat">
                <div class="lbl">Countries</div>
                <div class="n">32</div>
                <p>NavTour deployed across 32 countries, primarily Americas and Ibero-America.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-stat">
                <div class="lbl">Customers</div>
                <div class="n">500<span class="sym">+</span></div>
                <p>Revenue teams using NavTour to run their demo motions every week.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-stat">
                <div class="lbl">Setup time</div>
                <div class="n">2<span class="sym">min</span></div>
                <p>From account creation to first published demo. No dev ticket, no staging environment.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

@* ── P4 SUITE ── *@
<section class="nt-section" style="background:var(--nt-bg-alt)">
    <div class="nt-container" style="max-width:740px">
        <span class="eyebrow">Part of the P4 Software Cloud Suite</span>
        <h2 style="margin-top:16px">Built for the way enterprise software sells in the Americas.</h2>
        <p style="margin-top:20px;line-height:1.75">
            NavTour is one product in the P4 Software Cloud Suite — a collection of operational and revenue tools
            built for enterprise teams across Latin America. Our other products include P4 Warehouse (WMS),
            P4 Customs (import/export compliance), and CifraHQ (financial operations).
            NavTour connects natively to all of them.
        </p>
        <div style="margin-top:32px;display:flex;gap:24px;flex-wrap:wrap">
            <img src="/images/brand/p4warehouse-full.png" alt="P4 Warehouse" style="height:32px;opacity:0.7" />
            <img src="/images/brand/p4customs-full.png" alt="P4 Customs" style="height:32px;opacity:0.7" />
            <img src="/images/brand/cifrahq-full.png" alt="CifraHQ" style="height:32px;opacity:0.7" />
            <img src="/images/brand/navtour-full.png" alt="NavTour" style="height:32px;opacity:0.7" />
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<NtCTABand Headline="Built by practitioners, for practitioners."
           SubText="Join 500+ revenue teams using NavTour to turn buyer curiosity into closed deals."
           PrimaryLabel="Start free &rarr;"
           SecondaryLabel="Get in touch"
           SecondaryHref="/contact" />
